message.content:
We start by identifying the key figures (all amounts are the End_amount figures from the balance sheet):

1. Current Assets = 13,753,616.13  
   Current Liabilities = 5,515,978.61  

• Current Ratio = Current Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 13,753,616.13 / 5,515,978.61 ≈ 2.49  

2. Inventory = 7,832,820.00  
 Quick Assets = Current Assets – Inventory  
  = 13,753,616.13 – 7,832,820.00  
  = 5,920,796.13  
• Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 5,920,796.13 / 5,515,978.61 ≈ 1.07  

3. Total Assets = 21,662,106.19  
 Total Liabilities = (in this case, only current liabilities are provided) = 5,515,978.61  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 5,515,978.61 / 21,662,106.19 ≈ 0.25  

4. Owner's Equity = 16,146,127.58  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Owner's Equity  
  = 5,515,978.61 / 16,146,127.58 ≈ 0.34  

5. From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -2,419,019.09  
 For Debt here we use the total liabilities  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Liabilities  
  = -2,419,019.09 / 5,515,978.61 ≈ -0.44  

Thus, the final solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Current Ratio': '2.49', 'Quick Ratio': '1.07', 'Debt to Asset Ratio': '0.25', 'Debt to Equity Ratio': '0.34', 'Cash Flow to Debt Ratio': '-0.44'}}
